High Point Golf Club
12251 Club House Road, Brooksville, FL  34613      (352) 596-0833
Welcome, we’re so glad you stopped by!
High Point Golf Club, Inc. is a member owned, 501(c)(7) not-for-profit, private golf club, established in 1976.  The Club is self-governed by a nine-member
Board of Directors
elected by the membership.
Our members and their guests can enjoy the 18-hole, par 72 golf course that will challenge them on every tee, fairway and green.  Lined on both sides by lovely, manufactured homes, we feel our course continues to be one of the best maintained in the area.  When you come to look for your future retirement home, please let us take you out for a
free round of golf
so you can experience the thrill of playing High Point Golf Club.
More information about our wonderful 55+ Community can be found by clicking
here
.
We have:
NO TEE TIMES - you can just show up and start playing golf
NO TRAIL FEES for using your golf cart
REASONABLE ANNUAL FEES for Single & Family Memberships
MONTHLY MEMBERSHIPS for Seasonal Renters
GREEN FEE MEMBERSHIPS for the Occasional Golfers
WOMEN, MEN & MIXED/COUPLE Organized League Play
PRACTICE FACILITY with Driving Range & Putting Green
FULL-SERVICE BAR & RESTAURANT
SOCIAL MEMBERSHIPS for the non-golfers in High Point
GOLF & SOCIAL EVENTS throughout the year
High Point Café & Bar
Lunch is available from the Café    11 a.m. - 2 p.m.
Monday, Wednesday & Thursday
Tuesday night    5 p.m. - ???
Game Night
Thursday night Karaoke    5 p.m. - 9:00 p.m.
(Music licensing provided through

&

)
Friday night Games    5 p.m. - ???
Queen of Hearts Raffle
7 p.m. drawing
Show Me the Money
6:30 - 7:30 p.m.
For event additions, see our online calendar at the link above or visit High Point Golf Club or High Point Golf Club Cafe on Facebook.
High Point Pro Shop
The Pro Shop is open daily from 7 a.m. to Noon as volunteers are available.  We have a wide range of golf products including hats, towels, golf gloves, balls, clothing, etc.  Inventory changes often so it pays to stop in to visit frequently.  We are staffed by volunteers, so if you have a few hours to spare we welcome your help.

The Board of Directors of the High Point Golf Club invites you to visit our golf community.  We think you would enjoy all aspects of a golf membership in our Club.  If you or your spouse/partner/companion are not a golfer, we also offer a Social Membership.
As a Golf Member you can take advantage of playing our beautiful and challenging course.  If you can score well here, you can do well on any golf course!
As a Golf Member or Social Member, you are invited to enjoy the social aspects of our club, including our delicious lunches and dinners as scheduled.  We believe you would enjoy a good meal at a fair price with plenty of fellowship.  The Club sponsors Karaoke on Thursdays from 5-9, and we have numerous events & shows throughout the year.
Our Club and community are founded on a spirit of volunteerism.  There are a wide variety of activities for which you may want to volunteer and get to know other Club members.  We always need Pro-Shop counter attendants, golf course rangers, restaurant servers, and bartenders.
Our membership chairman,
Linda Schroeder
, will be glad to answer any questions regarding the club, volunteering, etc.
Come join us!  We look forward to seeing you!
2025 Membership Rates
Rules and Regulations May 2024
By Laws - Dec 2023
